  "body": "- [x] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nThe unit test contract has zero balance by default and that's why It's impossible to execute transactions.\r\nIt makes unit tests not as useful as they could be.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nTry to use `send` in a unit test.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nI expected them to have some initial ballance (like every account in testrpc has 100 ETH).\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nThey're empty.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: macos\r\n* Truffle version: 3.0.5\r\n* Ethereum client: testrpc\r\n* node version: v7.5.0\r\n* npm version: 4.1.2\r\n",
